1. Yep, that's it exactly, d0 is OR'd against the return.<br />2. On power on, the latch is not set, so yes $6000.d0 is 0<br /><br />Zepper: on second look, it is not always the high-byte of the address returned in the $6xxx region.<br /><br />$6000-61ff returns $60 or $61 (if latch set)<br />$6200-63ff returns $62 or $63 (^)<br />...<br />$6e00-6fff returns $6e or $6f<br /><br />The $7xxx region is "normal" though and always returns the high-byte of address<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=158">BootGod</a> — Sun Nov 06, 2011 6:59 am</p><hr />
